articles.author: Scott Neuman
articles.title: Europe Is Launching A Satellite Made of Plywood Into Space - NPR
articles.description: In Europe, engineers are planning to send a plywood-sheathed satellite into orbit to test how well the venerable construction material holds up in space.
articles.content:
WISA Woodsat, seen in an artist's rendering, is billed as the world's first wooden satellite. It's set to be launched from New Zealand before the end of the year.

articles.title: Soccer-UEFA reminds teams of sponsorship obligations after Ronaldo Coca-Cola case - The Star Online
articles.description: (Reuters) -European soccer's governing body UEFA has responded to Portugal forward Cristiano Ronaldo's removal of a Coca-Cola bottle at a Euro 2020 news conference by telling teams they have contractual obligations towards tournament sponsors.
